# The Future of Interaction

## Making the Whole World Interactive: Interaction at Scale
[Ivan Poupyrev](http://www.ivanpoupyrev.com/) (Google, formerly Disney Research)

How can we make **highly interactive physically collected** experiences at Disney parks?

An interaction system delivering great user experience over large geographical areas, in indoor and oudoor conditions, under direct sunlight and in near darkness, invisible to users, children, adult and idiot-proof, obscured be foliage, glass, paint, dust, etc., with no modification to existing infrastructure, requiring little to no maintenance, highly reliable, at a very low cost.

In other words, *interaction that scales in multiple dimensions.*

Examples:
- [Touché Sensor](http://www.disneyresearch.com/project/touche-touch-and-gesture-sensing-for-the-real-world/)
- [Paper Generators](http://www.disneyresearch.com/project/paper-generators/)

